original: Kroon, Erik Julius, e. provinsialläkare, Gravarne, f. 16/9/92 i Malmö av Johan K. o. Anna Andersson. G. 1. 22 m. Ellen Brorson, d. 32; 2. 41 m. Elin Sofia Carlsson. Barn: Kerstin f. 22, Ingrid 24, Margareta 25, Anna-Helena 27, Birgitta 31, Pär 32, Lars 43. — Stud:ex. i Malmö 11, med. kand. i Lund 19, med. lic. där 28. E. o. aman. v. anat. inst. i Lund 13, aman. v. med.-kem. inst. där 14, e. läk. i Tollarps, Rejmyre o. Strängnäs distr. 22-23, assist :läk. v. Malmö allm. sjukh. kir. avd. samt tf. und:läk. v. avd. f. förlossn. o. kvinnosjukd. där 24, tf. stadsdäk. i Laholm 25-26, e. läk. v. Västerviks, hosp. 27, tf. prov:iäk. i Hälleviksstrands distr. 28, munic:läk. i Graivarne 38, e. prov:’liäk. i Gravarne distr. sed. 45.
translated:
Kroon, Erik Julius, b. 16/9/92 in Malmö to Johan K. and Anna Andersson. Trained as a provincial physician. Married 1. in 1922 to Ellen Brorson, who passed away in 1932; married 2. in 1941 to Elin Sofia Carlsson. Children: Kerstin b. 1922, Ingrid b. 1924, Margareta b. 1925, Anna-Helena b. 1927, Birgitta b. 1931, Pär b. 1932, Lars b. 1943. 

Education: Graduated from high school in Malmö in 1911, obtained a Bachelor's degree in Medicine in Lund in 1919, and a Medical Licentiate degree there in 1928. 

Career: Temporary assistant at the Anatomy Institute in Lund 1913, assistant at the Medical-Chemistry Institute there in 1914, resident physician in Tollarps, Rejmyre, and Strängnäs districts from 1922 to 1923, assistant physician in the Surgical Department of Malmö General Hospital and acting undersurgeon in the department for childbirth and women's diseases there in 1924, acting city doctor in Laholm from 1925 to 1926, resident physician at Västervik Hospital in 1927, acting provincial physician in Hälleviksstrand district in 1928, municipal physician in Gravarne from 1938, and appointed provincial physician in Gravarne district since 1945.
